title: Dominican Republic  CPI Housing Utilities
description: CPI Housing Utilities in Dominican Republic increased to 120.62 points in October from 120.38 points in September of 2022. CPI Housing Utilities in Dominican Republic averaged 71.95 points from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 120.62 points in October of 2022 and a record low of 20.85 points in January of 1999. This page provides - Dominican Republic  Cpi Housing Utilities- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Dominican Republic
